        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 4 at 3:21PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 321 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 7 miles south of Blanca to 7 miles
southeast of Manassa, or extending from 19 miles east of San Luis
Valley Airport to 25 miles south of San Luis Valley Airport, moving
northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Manassa, Sanford, San Luis, Blanca, San Acacio, Mesita, San Pablo,
Sanchez Reservoir, Jaroso, Fort Garland, Chama, Garcia and
southern Spring Burn Scar south of Highway 160 in Costilla county.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
